            id="FAR_52_223_5">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">52.223-5</ph> Pollution Prevention and Right-to-Know Information.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody " outputclass="clause">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e8">As prescribed in <ph class="- topic/ph " outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF">
               <xref base="i1094212"
                     class="- topic/xref "
                     href="23.1005.dita#FAR_23_1005"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">23.1005</xref>
            </ph>, insert the following clause:</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e14" outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps">Pollution Prevention and Right-to-Know Information <ph class="- topic/ph " outputclass="SmCaps">(May 2011)</ph>
         </p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d3337e25">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e20">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(a)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Definitions</i>. As used in this clause-</p>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e26"/>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e27">
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "
                     outputclass="Term"
                     xtrc="d3372e42"
                     xtrf="_52.223-5">Toxic chemical</i> means a chemical or chemical category listed in 40 CFR372.65.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e32">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(b)</ph>
						            Federal facilities are required to comply with the provisions of the Emergency Planning and Community Right-to-Know Act of 1986 (EPCRA) (<xref class="- topic/xref "
                        format="html"
                        href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external">42U.S. C.11001-11050</xref>), and the Pollution Prevention Act of 1990 (PPA) (<xref class="- topic/xref "
                        format="html"
                        href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external">42U.S. C.13101-13109</xref>).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e43">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(c)</ph>
						            The Contractor shall provide all information needed by the Federal facility to comply with the following:</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d3337e70">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e49">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(1)</ph>
								                The emergency planning reporting requirements of Section 302 of EPCRA.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e54">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(2)</ph>
								                The emergency notice requirements of Section 304 of EPCRA.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e59">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(3)</ph>
								                The list of Material Safety Data Sheets, required by Section 311 of EPCRA.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e64">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(4)</ph>
								                The emergency and hazardous chemical inventory forms of Section 312 of EPCRA.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e69">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(5)</ph>
								                The toxic chemical release inventory of Section 313 of EPCRA, which includes the reduction and recycling information required by Section 6607 of PPA.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3376e74">
                        <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">(6)</ph>
								                The toxic chemical and hazardous substance release and use reduction goals of section 2(e) of Executive Order 13423 and of Executive Order 13514.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="Endofclause">(End of clause)</p>
         <section class="- topic/section " outputclass="Alternate"><?FM MARKER [Alt] Start?>
            <p class="- topic/p " id="d3379e80">
               <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate I </i>
               <ph outputclass="SmCaps">(May 2011)</ph>. As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
                  <xref base="i1094212"
                        class="- topic/xref "
                        href="23.1005.dita#FAR_23_1005"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">23.1005</xref>
               </ph>(b), add the following paragraph (c)(7) to the basic clause:</p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List1">(c)(7) The environmental management system as described in section 3(b) of E.O. 13423 and 2(j) of E.O. 13514.</p>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] End?>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] Start?>
            <p class="- topic/p " id="d3372e96">
               <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate II </i>
               <ph outputclass="SmCaps">(May 2011)</ph>. As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
                  <xref base="i1094212"
                        class="- topic/xref "
                        href="23.1005.dita#FAR_23_1005"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">23.1005</xref>
               </ph>(c), add the following paragraph (c)(7) to the basic clause. If Alternate I is also prescribed, renumber paragraph (c)(7) as paragraph (c)(8).</p>
            <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="List1">(c)(7) The facility compliance audits as described in section 3(c) of E.O. 13423.</p>
            <?FM MARKER [Alt] End?>
         </section>
